President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Micah Fialka-Feldman, a teaching assistant at Syracuse University, will be appointed as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities. Betty Williams, a Consumer Education and Training Coordinator at The Arc of Indiana, will also be appointed to the committee. Elie Wiesel, the President and Co-Founder of The Elie Wiesel Foundation for Humanity, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Dr. Donald L. Pereira, Chief of the Section of Fisheries at the Minnesota Department of Natural Resources, will be appointed as Commissioner of the United States Section of the Great Lakes Fishery Commission. Tod Sedgwick, a Fellow at the Transatlantic Center at The Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Study, will be appointed as a member of the World War I Centennial Commission.